# Preparatory Exercises – Phase Change of Water

## Understanding Check Questions (1–4)

### 1. Heating of Ice
Data:
m = 0.10 kg
cp,ice = 2200 J/(kg·K)
Ti = –20°C → Tf = 0°C
P = 300 W

Calculation:
Q = m·cp,ice·ΔT  
= 0.10 · 2200 · (0 – (–20))  
= 4.40·10^3 J

t = Q / P  
= 4.40·10^3 / 300 ≈ 14.7 s

Answer: Q ≈ 4.4 kJ, t ≈ 15 s



### 2. Melting of Ice
Lf = 3.33·10^5 J/kg

Q = m·Lf  
= 0.10 · 3.33·10^5  
= 3.33·10^4 J

t = Q / P  
= 3.33·10^4 / 300 ≈ 111 s

Answer: Q ≈ 33 kJ, t ≈ 110 s



### 3. Heating of Water
cp,water = 4180 J/(kg·K)  
Ti = 0°C → Tf = 100°C

Q = m·cp,water·ΔT  
= 0.10 · 4180 · 100  
= 4.18·10^4 J

t = Q / P  
= 4.18·10^4 / 300 ≈ 139 s

Answer: Q ≈ 42 kJ, t ≈ 140 s



### 4. Vaporization of Water
Lv = 2.26·10^6 J/kg

Q = m·Lv  
= 0.10 · 2.26·10^6  
= 2.26·10^5 J

t = Q / P  
= 2.26·10^5 / 300 ≈ 752 s

Answer: Q ≈ 226 kJ, t ≈ 12.5 min



## Theory Exercises (1–3)

Assumptions and data:
m_i1 = 0.10 kg  
m_w = 1.0 kg  
m_g = 0.10 kg  
cp,ice = 2200 J/(kg·K)  
cp,water = 4180 J/(kg·K)  
cp,glass = 840 J/(kg·K)  
Lf = 3.33·10^5 J/kg  
Ti = –20°C  
Tf = 0°C  
T_water_initial = 20°C  
P = 300 W



### Theory Exercise 1 - Find equilibrium temperature T_water_final
(m_i1·cp,ice·(0 – (–20)))
+ (m_i1·Lf)
+ (m_i1·cp,water·(T_water_final – 0))
+ ((m_g·cp,glass + m_w·cp,water)·(T_water_final – 20)) = 0

Solution:  
T_water_final ≈ 10°C

Answer: ≈ 10°C



### Theory Exercise 2 - Find mass of additional ice m_i2 needed to reach 0°C
Q_released = (m_g·cp,glass + (m_w + m_i1)·cp,water) · (0 – T_water_final)  
Q_absorbed = m_i2·cp,ice·(0 – (–20)) + m_i2·Lf  

Energy balance:  
Q_released + Q_absorbed = 0  

Solution:  
m_i2 ≈ 0.13 kg

Answer: m_i2 ≈ 0.13 kg



### Theory Exercise 3  - Find time t to heat the system to 20°C after adding m_i2
m_total = m_w + m_i1 + m_i2  
= 1.23 kg

C = m_total·cp,water + m_g·cp,glass

Q = C · (20 – 0)

t = Q / P ≈ 347 s

Answer: t ≈ 350 s (≈ 5.8 min)

